   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🧠 Machine Learning Analysis of Two Timed Tasks\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook performs a full ML pipeline on within-subject timed task data, covering:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Data Setup & Exploration** — load, simulate, or paste your data\n",
    "2. **Statistical Baseline** — paired t-test for reference\n",
    "3. **Logistic Regression** — supervised binary classification\n",
    "4. **Support Vector Machine (SVM)** — supervised, finds optimal decision boundary\n",
    "5. **Random Forest** — supervised, with feature importance\n",
    "6. **K-Means Clustering** — unsupervised grouping\n",
    "7. **PCA** — unsupervised dimensionality reduction & visualization\n",
    "8. **Model Comparison** — ROC curves, AUC, accuracy summary\n",
    "\n",
    "> 📌 **To use your own data:** Replace the simulated data in Cell 2 with your own values."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b2c3d4e5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Install & Import Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c3d4e5f6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install dependencies if needed\n",
    "# !pip install numpy pandas matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn scipy\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import polars as pl\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy import stats\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sklearn - supervised\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import SVC\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score, StratifiedKFold\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    classification_report, confusion_matrix,\n",
    "    roc_curve, auc, RocCurveDisplay\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sklearn - unsupervised\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score\n",
    "\n",
    "# Aesthetics\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', palette='muted', font_scale=1.1)\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 110\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('✅ Libraries loaded successfully')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d4e5f6a7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
